                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/752: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-18T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 18, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Repeat your 21, May 17, noon, to Buenos Aires for Braden<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d188fn8">Spruille Braden, American delegate to the Chaco Peace
                        Conference; see <ref target="#pg_35">pp. 35</ref> ff.</note> as well as all
                    subsequent telegrams reporting important developments in the political
                    situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
